=== Step 7 — verdict ===
NO-OP. The premise (codegen emits both canonical .global form AND a redundant non-.global stub) does not match the codebase. The codegen emits ONE mnemonic per op-key, and the suffix is `.shared` (RFC 067 P2 design — load/store fragments through a 2048 B `_hexa_wmma_stage` shared-memory slot, not direct global-memory access).

Possible task-premise interpretations and their honest-scope dispositions:
  (a) Task meant to delete `.shared` from the wmma load/store mnemonics
      → REJECT: `.shared` is required by PTX ISA §9.7.13.4 when the
        address operand references a `.shared` slot. Removing it would
        make ptxas reject the instruction.
  (b) Task meant to add a `.global` direct-load variant (skip staging)
      → SCOPE-CHANGE not cleanup: would touch 3+ functions + Case 23
        + per-op offset logic. Out of scope for a single-session cosmetic edit.
  (c) Task meant to remove duplicate emit between L459-462 and L1100-1136
      → REJECT: L1100-1136 is the P3 family-keyed extension (bf16 / f16-acc).
        L459-462 is the PR #150 backward-compat default. They handle
        DIFFERENT (op, dtype, layout) tuples; the family table dispatches
        to the canonical table at L1103 when dtype/layout are empty.
        No duplication.

